{
  "id": "019d2827-6bdc-7051-b52a-b52ef63d1e3a",
  "content": "# Decision: Phase 2 CI Quality Gate Implementation (2026-03-26)\n\n## What\nImplemented the CI quality gate for RAG retrieval evaluation:\n- `benchmarks/ci/eval-gate.sh` — runs eval suite, checks thresholds, writes JSON summary\n- `benchmarks/ci/format-pr-comment.py` — formats results as markdown PR comment with delta vs baseline\n- `.github/workflows/eval-gate.yml` — GitHub Actions workflow triggered on PRs touching retrieval code\n\n## Thresholds (floor values, not targets)\n- MRR >= 0.40 (baseline: 0.544)\n- Source Recall@5 >= 0.30 (baseline: 0.375)\n- Keyword Recall >= 0.50 (baseline: 0.65)\n- Query Timeouts <= 3\n\n## Key Design Choices\n- JSON summary written to `/tmp/eval-summary.json` (not repo tree) to avoid accidental commits\n- HTML comment marker `<!-- eval-gate-comment -->` for idempotent PR comment replacement\n- Metrics extracted via Python JSON parsing (not `eval`) to avoid shell injection\n- Timeout detection uses substring match (`\"timed out\" in error`) not exact match\n- Stale results cleaned before each run (`rm -f eval-*.json`)\n- Workflow uses `if: always()` on failure step to prevent silent swallowing\n- Post-ingestion entry count validation prevents running evals against empty data\n- Path triggers include server, kernel, inference crates, benchmarks, and corvia.toml\n\n## Workflow triggers on\n- `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-server/src/**`\n- `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-kernel/**`\n- `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-inference/**`\n- `benchmarks/**`\n- `corvia.toml`",
